        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Hi,\r\n\r\nat the moment, there is no css-catchable structure for elements (and their labels) which are not valid.\r\nA {{<ul>}} tag is appended to the element DOM Node, but you can not add f.e. a red border for this input element with css-only.\r\n\r\nThis is what the Decorators produce:\r\n{code}\r\n<dt id=\"sender_name-label\">\r\n    <label for=\"sender_name\" class=\"required\">Name<\/label>\r\n<\/dt>\r\n<dd id=\"sender_name-element\">\r\n    <input type=\"text\" name=\"sender_name\" id=\"sender_name\" value=\"\" class=\"text\" \/>\r\n    <ul class=\"errors\">\r\n        <li>Enter at least 1 character.<\/li>\r\n    <\/ul>\r\n<\/dd>\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nAnd this is what I suggest:\r\n{code}\r\n<dt id=\"sender_name-label\" class=\"invalid\">\r\n    <label for=\"sender_name\" class=\"required\">Name<\/label>\r\n<\/dt>\r\n<dd id=\"sender_name-element\" class=\"invalid\">\r\n    <input type=\"text\" name=\"sender_name\" id=\"sender_name\" value=\"\" class=\"text\" \/>\r\n    <ul class=\"errors\">\r\n        <li>Enter at least 1 character.<\/li>\r\n    <\/ul>\r\n<\/dd>\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n(I added a css class to the {{<dt>}} and {{<dd>}} tag)\r\n\r\nWithout that, I have to write my own Decorator to do that, which is not really necessary, if the Default Decorator would add this information to the relevant DOM Nodes."
        },
